    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.652/133: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-06T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 6, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6—2:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>503. Department’s 188, December 4, 4 p.m. As regards article 20, the Italian
                    authorities suggest that their point of view would be taken care of by the
                    addition of the phrase “and the Italian possessions and colonies” after the
                    phrase “except the Panama Canal Zone” in the original American draft of this
                    article. They also inquire whether under this condition the American Government
                    would later wish to exclude its possessions and colonies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
